Package com.pandora.general.objects

package com.pandora.general.objects
This package contains classes representing various objects used in the Pandora biogeochemical model for freshwater systems. These objects include base objects, cells, cell timesteps, Pandora timesteps, differential equations, and other related entities.

The key classes in this package are:

  • AbstractBaseObject: An abstract base class for common properties of Pandora model objects.
  • Cell: Represents a geographical cell in the Pandora model with attributes such as center coordinates, surface area, and next cell identifier.
  • CellTimestep: Represents a time step associated with a geographical cell, including initial and final states, and timestamps.
  • PandoraDifferentialEquations: Implements the FirstOrderDifferentialEquations interface for solving differential equations in the Pandora model.
  • PandoraTimestep: Represents a time step in the Pandora model with attributes such as initial values, time range, and sources.
  • River: Represents a river in the Pandora model with a list of independent cell sets associated with it.
  • RiverTimestep: Represents a time step associated with a river, containing a list of independent cell timesteps.

The classes in this package are designed to model and support the simulation of biogeochemical processes in freshwater systems using the Pandora model.

  • Classes
    Class
    Description
    AbstractBaseObject
    The AbstractBaseObject is an abstract class providing a base structure for objects with a unique identifier (id) and a name.
    Cell
    The Cell class extends AbstractBaseObject and represents a geographical cell with a unique identifier, name, and additional properties such as center latitude, center longitude, surface area, and the identifier of the next cell in the sequence.
    CellTimestep
    The CellTimestep class extends AbstractBaseObject and represents a specific time step associated with a geographical cell.
    PandoraDifferentialEquations
    The PandoraDifferentialEquations class implements the FirstOrderDifferentialEquations interface and represents the differential equations governing the Pandora model for a specific time step.
    PandoraTimestep
    The PandoraTimestep class represents a specific time step in the Pandora model, characterized by initial values, start and end times, dimensionality, discharge, volume, terrestrial and upstream sources, and other properties.
    River
    The River class extends AbstractBaseObject and represents a river entity characterized by a unique identifier, name, and a list of independent cell sets associated with the river.
    RiverTimestep
    The RiverTimestep class extends AbstractBaseObject and represents a river timestep entity with a unique identifier, name, and a list of independent cell timesteps associated with the river timestep.
